Iavan Pijoos, News24(ER24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - Four people were killed and one injured when two vehicles collided on the N1 before the Kroonvaal Toll Plaza, paramedics said on Sunday.ER24 spokesperson Werner Vermaak said three men died in one of the vehicles, which was found on the highway. &nbsp;Another person in a car found in the nearby veld had also died, while an occupant in the same vehicle was wounded.The wounded person was rushed to a hospital in Parys.&nbsp;The cause of the crash was being investigated.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.